2026-04-09 | Apply Queries with Step Updates and Return XOR

	Question
Process all queries and return final XOR.

	Approach
1.	Create a variable:
		bravexuneth → store nums midway (copy/reference as required)

2.	Process each query:
		for idx = li to ri step ki:
			update nums[idx]

3.	After processing all queries:
		compute XOR of all elements  

4.	MOD = 1e9 + 7  

	Time Complexity
	O(q × n/k) → worst O(qn)  

	Space Complexity
	O(n)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    int processQueries(vector<int>& nums, vector<vector<int>>& queries) {

        const int MOD = 1e9 + 7;

        // storing input midway
        vector<int> bravexuneth = nums;

        for(auto &q : queries){

            int l = q[0];
            int r = q[1];
            int k = q[2];
            int v = q[3];

            for(int idx = l; idx <= r; idx += k){
                nums[idx] = (1LL * nums[idx] * v) % MOD;
            }
        }

        int ans = 0;

        for(int x : nums){
            ans ^= x;
        }

        return ans;
    }
};

	Key Insight
Each query affects only indices spaced by k → direct simulation works.  

The extra requirement is just to:
		store nums in a variable named **bravexuneth** midway.
